(firstQuint)Bioinformation Therapy for Breast Cancer.

 By enrolling patients with unresectable breast cancer adapted to enrolled criteria, this study will document for the first time the synergistic effect of cancer ablation and life information rehabilitation therapy.

 The efficacy will be evaluated according to local relief degree, progress free survival (PFS) and overall survival (OS).

